CRITICAL: Create a library of verified, executable skills (not just patterns).

## Inspiration
- Voyager: Ever-growing skill library of executable code
- Skills are verified before adding, compositional, reusable

## Key Difference from Current Design
Current: Store patterns as text/vectors
New: Store EXECUTABLE CODE that can be invoked

## Skill Definition
```typescript
interface Skill {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  description: string;

  // Executable implementation
  implementation: {
    type: 'bash' | 'typescript' | 'mcp_tool' | 'composite';
    code: string;           // Actual executable code
    entrypoint?: string;    // For TS: function name
    dependencies?: string[]; // npm packages, other skills
  };

  // Input/Output schema
  inputSchema: JSONSchema;
  outputSchema: JSONSchema;

  // Verification
  verification: {
    testCases: TestCase[];
    successCriteria: string;
    lastVerifiedAt: Date;
    verificationScore: number;
  };

  // Metadata
  triggers: string[];        // NL patterns that invoke this skill
  composedFrom?: string[];   // Skills this builds on
  usageCount: number;
  successRate: number;
  avgDuration: number;
  createdBy: 'human' | 'orchestrator';
  createdAt: Date;
}
```

## Skill Creation Flow (from Voyager)
```
1. Identify need for skill (during task or post-mortem)
2. Generate skill code (LLM)
3. Execute skill in sandbox
4. Verify success (self-verification)
5. If failed:
   - Analyze error
   - Refine code (iterative prompting)
   - Retry (max 3 iterations)
6. If verified:
   - Add to skill library
   - Index for retrieval
7. If failed after retries:
   - Log failure for human review
   - Don't add to library
```

## Self-Verification
```typescript
interface VerificationResult {
  success: boolean;
  output: any;
  errors: string[];
  sideEffects: string[];  // Files created, commands run
  duration: number;
  cost: number;
}

// Verify skill works as expected
async function verifySKill(skill: Skill): Promise<VerificationResult> {
  for (const testCase of skill.verification.testCases) {
    const result = await executeSkill(skill, testCase.input);
    if (\!matchesExpected(result, testCase.expected)) {
      return { success: false, ... };
    }
  }
  return { success: true, ... };
}
```

