ADAPTED FOR TERMINAL MODEL: Reflexion happens OFFLINE via transcript analysis, not real-time.

## Original Concept (Real-time)
Actor → Evaluator → Self-Reflect → Inject cues → Improved Actor
This assumed direct context injection, which doesn't work with terminal CLIs.

## Adapted Concept (Offline)
```
Session completes
       │
       ▼
┌─────────────────┐
│ Read Transcript │
└─────────────────┘
       │
       ▼
┌─────────────────┐
│ Evaluator       │  Score the session: success/partial/failure
│ (Offline)       │  Identify what went well/poorly
└─────────────────┘
       │
       ▼
┌─────────────────┐
│ Self-Reflection │  Generate verbal learnings
│ (Offline)       │  'Agent spent too long searching for X'
└─────────────────┘
       │
       ▼
┌─────────────────┐
│ Config Updates  │  Apply learnings to NEXT session
│ (Skills, Docs)  │  Not current session
└─────────────────┘
```

## Three Components (Adapted)

### 1. Evaluator Service
Analyzes completed transcripts:
```typescript
interface TranscriptEvaluation {
  sessionId: string;

  // Scoring
  taskCompletionScore: number;  // 0-1
  efficiencyScore: number;      // 0-1 (tokens used vs typical)
  errorScore: number;           // 0-1 (errors encountered)

  // Qualitative
  whatWorked: string[];
  whatFailed: string[];
  inefficiencies: string[];

  // Classification
  outcome: 'success' | 'partial' | 'failure' | 'interrupted';
}
```

### 2. Self-Reflection Service
Generates verbal learnings from evaluation:
```typescript
interface Reflection {
  sessionId: string;
  evaluationId: string;

  // Verbal cues (like Reflexion paper)
  reflections: string[];
  // e.g., 'The agent wasted 5 turns searching for database config. 
  //        Add db location to CLAUDE.md.'

  // Actionable improvements
  suggestedActions: SuggestedAction[];
}
```

### 3. Improvement Application
Apply reflections to config:
```typescript
interface SuggestedAction {
  type: 'add_to_claudemd' | 'create_skill' | 'add_gotcha' | 'create_tool';
  description: string;
  implementation: string;
  confidence: number;
}
```

## Key Insight
Reflexion in terminal model is 'verbal reinforcement learning' applied BETWEEN sessions, not within them. The agent in the next session benefits from learnings stored in config files and skills.

